{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: a mocked generator can always return a perfect contextual reply and miss real model drift into generic text. LLM-DEP: correctness depends on real LLM output quality and variability, not just prompt wiring.","test_description":"Run the real drafting model on a representative set of real email threads. For each run, score whether the draft includes concrete thread-specific details (names, requested actions, dates) and fails if it is generic. Repeat multiple times per thread to catch nondeterministic regressions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"If contradiction detection uses model judgment, mocking the checker hides real false negatives/positives. This is a quality-of-classification boundary, so real model behavior is required.","test_description":"Provide drafts with known contradictory and non-contradictory claims against a real KB, run the real consistency checker, and assert contradiction flags meet a minimum precision/recall threshold across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The key failure is hallucination behavior under missing evidence. A mock can force disclaimer output and miss fabrication risk. This depends on real LLM generation behavior.","test_description":"Use threads where retrieval returns no relevant KB entries, run real draft generation, and assert the draft includes the required uncertainty/disclaimer language and does not introduce unsupported factual claims; repeat to capture variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit tests can miss wiring/state bugs between draft state, approval state, and send trigger. Real LLM output is not required to validate this guardrail; integrated modules and local persistence/eventing are enough.","test_description":"In an integrated test with real workflow components (state store + send trigger path) and a test mail transport, verify no send call occurs before explicit approval, then verify a send occurs only after approval.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is explicitly a multi-step pipeline with multiple agentic stages (generation and factual judgment), plus real thread ingestion and approval gating. Lower-level tests cannot expose cross-step interaction failures.","test_description":"Execute the full pipeline in staging on a real email thread: ingest thread, generate with real LLM, run real fact check against KB, present for approval, verify no send before approval, approve, then verify send and trace logs for each step.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
